ns2:Operation.description: Restrict the graph to concept codes (source and target) that originate from the supplied code system. Note: edges defined by other code systems will still be resolved if associated with both source and target nodes for the restricted code system.
ns2:Operation.name: restrictToSourceCodeSystem

ns2:Operation.description: Restrict the graph to edges that have concepts derived from the supplied code system as a target.
ns2:Operation.name: restrictToTargetCodeSystem

ns2:Operation.description: Restrict the graph to concept codes (source and target) that originate from the supplied code system. Note: edges defined by other code systems will still be resolved if associated with both source and target nodes for the restricted code system.
ns2:Operation.name: restrictToCodeSystem

ns2:Operation.description: Restrict the graph to associations that have one of the codes in the supplied list as target codes.
ns2:Operation.name: restrictToTargetCodes

ns2:Operation.description: Restrict the graph to associations that have one of the codes in the supplied list as source codes.
ns2:Operation.name: restrictToSourceCodes

ns2:Operation.description: Restrict the graph to the nodes that participate as a source or target of an association whose directional name matches the one provided and, if supplied, * the named association qualifiers. * A directional name is considered to be either the forward or reverse label * registered to an association defined by the ontology. Forward and reverse names * are optionally assigned to each association. For example, an association 'lineage' may have a forward name 'ancestorOf' and reverse name 'descendentOf'.
ns2:Operation.name: restrictToDirectionalNames

ns2:Operation.description: Restrict the graph to the nodes that participate as a source or target of the named association and, if supplied, the named association qualifiers.
ns2:Operation.name: restrictToAssociations

ns2:Operation.description: Return a graph that contains only the codes that are present in the supplied list, and all edges that still have a source and target code remaining.
ns2:Operation.name: restrictToCodes

ns2:Operation.description: Return the set of concepts and associations that are present in both graphs.
ns2:Operation.name: intersect

ns2:Operation.description: Return the union of the two graphs. Union, in this context, means that the resulting graph contains the unique set of coded entries (String independent) that are present in one or both of the graphs, and the unique combination of edges (associations) present in one or both of the graphs.
ns2:Operation.name: union

ns2:Operation.description: Determine whether the supplied concept code is in the graph.
ns2:Operation.name: isCodeInGraph

ns2:Operation.description: Transform the graph into a simple of list of concept codes, removing all association information.
ns2:Operation.name: toNodeList

ns2:Operation.description: Determine whether there is an directed edge (or transitive closure of an edge) from the source code to the target code in this graph. The last parameter determines whether only direct associations are considered or whether the transitive closure of the edge is used.
ns2:Operation.name: areCodesRelated

ns2:Operation.description: Return the coding schemes who supported association matching with associationName. The search is performed only for loaded coding schemes. *
ns2:Operation.name: getCodingSchemesWithSupportedAssociation

ns2:Operation.description: Returns the identifiers for hierarchical relationships available for navigation within a coding scheme. These identifiers can be submitted to the getHierarchyBroader() or getHierarchyNarrower() methods to navigate corresponding tree structures. Possible return values are defined by the LexBIG model (see http://informatics.mayo.edu/LexGrid/downloads/LexGrid%20Model/schemas/2009/01/EAwebpublish/index.htm).
ns2:Operation.name: getHierarchyIDs

ns2:Operation.description: Indicates if the given code is considered retired or inactive within context of the provided scheme.
ns2:Operation.name: isCodeRetired

ns2:Operation.description: Return the forward name for the identified association.
ns2:Operation.name: getAssociationForwardName

ns2:Operation.description: Return all the association forward name for the coding scheme.
ns2:Operation.name: getAssociationForwardNames

ns2:Operation.description: Return the reverse name for the identified association.
ns2:Operation.name: getAssociationReverseName

ns2:Operation.description: Return all the association reverse name for the coding scheme.
ns2:Operation.name: getAssociationReverseNames

ns2:Operation.description: Return true if directionalName is the forward name of an association for the coding scheme.
ns2:Operation.name: isForwardName

ns2:Operation.description: Return true if directionalName is the reverse name of an association for the coding scheme.
ns2:Operation.name: isReverseName

ns2:Operation.description: Return a representation of associations between a concept and its immediate decendents. The resolved association list represents the next branch of the hierarchy when visualized in a top (root) to bottom (leaf) representation.
ns2:Operation.name: getHierarchyLevelNext

ns2:Operation.description: Return a representation of associations between a concept and its immediate ancestor(s). The resolved association list represents the previous level of the hierarchy when visualized in a top (root) to bottom (leaf) representation.
ns2:Operation.name: getHierarchyLevelPrev

ns2:Operation.description: Return a representation of associations between a concept and hierarchical root node(s). The resolved association list represents the path within the hierarchy from traversed from bottom (leaf) to top (root).
ns2:Operation.name: getHierarchyPathToRoot

ns2:Operation.description: Returns all root nodes for the given hierarchy and coding scheme. Each root concept represents the conceptual start or narrowest point of a tree when visualizing the hierarchy.
ns2:Operation.name: getHierarchyRoots

ns2:Operation.description: Returns all root nodes for the given hierarchy as a CodeNodeSet, which can be further restricted. Each root concept represents the conceptual start or narrowest point of a tree when visualizing the hierarchy.
ns2:Operation.name: getHierarchyRootSet

ns2:Operation.description: Create a CodedNodeSet from a set of concept codes in a coding scheme.
ns2:Operation.name: createCodeNodeSet

ns2:Operation.description: Return all the association forward name and reverse name for the coding scheme.
ns2:Operation.name: getAssociationForwardAndReverseNames

ns2:Operation.description: Return the copyright text for the coding scheme.
ns2:Operation.name: getCodingSchemeCopyright

ns2:ServiceContext.description: An iterator for retrieving Resolved coding scheme references.
ns2:ServiceContext.name: ResolvedConceptReferencesIterator

ns2:Operation.description: Return the next available concept reference, in order, from the underlying list. Note: This is effectively the same as performing next(1), but eliminates the need to continually unwrap the concept reference from the resolved list.
ns2:Operation.name: next

ns2:Operation.description: Return concept references from the underlying list, in order and up to the specified maximum.
ns2:Operation.name: nextInt

ns2:Operation.description: Return concept references from the underlying list, from the start point (inclusive) to the end point (exclusive). Calling this method has no effect on the next() calls - next() will still iterate * through the results in the same sequential order regardless of if this method has * been used. * * the result of numberRemaining() is not affected by calls to this method. * * Note: This method may return fewer results than requested even if there are still more results after the last result returned by the service. Note: The method is optional, and may not be implemented by all implementations. Note: Using this method in combination with Filters may cause significant performance reductions.
ns2:Operation.name: get

ns2:Operation.description: Return the next batch of resolved concept references.
ns2:Operation.name: scroll
